      <section eId="sec_CCP-1764">
        <num>CCP 1764</num>
        <heading>1764.  Peremptory challenges</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCP-1764__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>If trial is by a jury of six, each side is allowed three peremptory challenges.  If there is more than one party on any side, the court may allow each side additional peremptory challenges, not to exceed two.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-1764__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>If trial is by a jury of twelve, each side is allowed six peremptory challenges.  If there is more than one party on any side, the court may allow each side additional peremptory challenges, not to exceed four.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-1764__subsec_C">
          <num>C.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Each side shall be allowed an equal number of peremptory challenges.  If the parties on a side are unable to agree upon the allocation of peremptory challenges among themselves, the allocation shall be determined by the court before the examination on the voir dire.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=111300</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
